As we saw it, we had three options.  (a)Tell him we didn't need his help, and kill it without him, thus ensuring that if he dropped a scale it would go to a warrior in Vision. (b)Tell him thanks for the info, you're welcome to assist us and in return you'll be given a MORE THAN FAIR chance at the scale, or (c)Tell him he can help, but he's not getting a shot at the scale.<br>
<br>
We choose (b) because Allamar agreed with me that it was the right thing to do.  How many other guilds would have chosen (a) or (c)?<br>
<br>
