<br>
We've tested a point system for the guild as a whole, and we've found, overall, that it didn't work for us.  From time to a time a member suggets it, and when presented with the reasons it didn't work for us last time, they're generally unable to make it work for us.<br>
<br>
OTOH, there are some individual spawns that drop multi-class loot that we are experimenting with specific &quot;scorekeeping&quot; systems.  We use a by class point total for Scout Charisa, and thusfar, it works well.  Every time a member of your class attends a kill, that class scores a point, and when your class it on top of the list, your class loots it and loses a group's worth of points.  We still think it's fairer than individual point keeping for the spawn, and it's settled all discussion about who's turn it was to hand the item in or loot the reward.  [The wizards are, of course, secretly plotting to take the next four or five loots and make robes out of spite...]  We've never yet had a problem where the clerics (or any other class) in attendance couldn't decide which one of them should get the item, or disgruntled clerics getting upset that their points get &quot;spent&quot; while they're offline.<br>
<br>
Every system has flaws.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> However, bottom line: If you don't like the loot rules, you don't have to join Vision. It seems to work for Vision just fine.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
